 Prepare your ingredients before you do anything else. Get out a pan, a bowl, a fork, a turner, and a knife and spoon for the peanut butter and jelly. Crack some eggs in a bowl and whip it up just like you would do when making french toast. Make sure there is enough to make the amount of rolls you want. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/92\/Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/92\/Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Take a piece of bread and spread peanut butter over half of one side and jelly over the other. Or, if you like jelly in every bite, feel free to put as much as you want on. Carefully roll up the bread. On the crust that's on the end and is supposed to "seal it" put some peanut butter there and it will stay. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/3\/30\/Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/3\/30\/Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Get some butter in a heated pan. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/eb\/Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/eb\/Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Make the rolls! Dip the rolls in the egg mixture. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f6\/Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f6\/Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-Peanut-Butter-and-Jelly-French-Toast-Rolls-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

